quran[23]{c,v,t}:
  89,1,"By the dawn."
  89,2,"By the ten nights."
  89,3,"By the even and the odd."
  89,4,"By the night as it passes—"
  89,5,"is there in that a sworn oath for whoever has a mind{1}?",footnotes:1:A rational person.
  89,6,"Have you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>not seen what your Lord did to ʻĀd{1}—",footnotes:1:The pagan tribe of Prophet Hûd.
  89,7,"Iram,<i class=""s"">(the city) </i>of the pillars"
  89,8,"whose like has never been created in the lands;"
  89,9,"and Thamûd{1}, who carved the rocks in the valley;",footnotes:1:The pagan tribe of Prophet Salih.
  89,10,"and Pharaoh of the stakes?"
  89,11,"They<i class=""s"">(all) </i>exceeded all limits in the lands"
  89,12,"and spread much corruption therein,"
  89,13,"so your<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>Lord poured down upon them a scourge of punishment;"
  89,14,"indeed, your Lord is certainly ever-watchful."
  89,15,"So, as for man, whenever his Lord tries him through honoring and blessing him, he says, “My Lord has honored me.”"
  89,16,"But whenever He tries him through <span class=""h"">restricting<sup foot_note=""81469"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>his provision, he says, “My Lord has insulted me.”"
  89,17,"But no! Rather, <span class=""h"">you</span><a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a><span class=""h"">do not honor<sup foot_note=""81470"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">the orphan,</span>"
  89,18,"<span class=""h"">and you do not urge one another<sup foot_note=""81471"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">to</span><i class=""s"">(serve) </i><span class=""h"">food to the destitute</span><a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a><span class=""h"">,</span>"
  89,19,"<span class=""h"">and you devour inheritance</span><i class=""s"">(of the vulnerable) </i><span class=""h"">greedily,</span>"
  89,20,"<span class=""h"">and you love</span>wealth immensely."
  89,21,"But no! When the earth is pounded to dust, pounding after pounding;"
  89,22,"and your<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>Lord comes with the angels, rank after rank;"
  89,23,"and on that day, Hell is made to come forward—on that day man reminds himself, but how will reminding avail him?"
